<DocsLayout title="Encoding Presets">
  <h1>Encoding Presets</h1>
  <p>
    Encoding presets are named, reusable bundles of FFmpeg parameters that define the codec, quality settings, filters, and container format for an encode. Presets can be selected in the web UI, referenced in flow nodes, or passed directly to the API. EncodeSwarmr ships with a set of carefully tuned built-in presets; you can also create custom presets from scratch or by cloning a built-in.
  </p>

